# Using Resources

<div style="background-color: #C6E3E7; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px;"> <p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px;">
<b>Using resources</b> is a core, authentic practice of computer science.  Whether novice or expert, all programmers rely on code documentation and other resources when writing programs.
</p></div>

<img src="https://images.code.org/e7be9e7d1044b2ae78871193f71cbb66-image-1628699169394.jpg" alt="Two students working on the same laptop computer." width="350px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin-left:25px; margin-right:25px; margin-top:25px; margin-bottom:25px;">

## What is my role as the teacher?

#### Your role as the teacher is to help students develop the skill of finding answers on their own, rather than directly solving their problems for them. 

<div style="clear:both;">

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">‚ùì How is using resources related to the problem solving process?</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p>


* #### **Define** - Describe what you need to know.
* #### **Prepare** - Decide where to look for the information.
* #### **Try** - Read the resources.
* #### **Reflect** - Think about what worked.
</p></div></details>


<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">üß∞ What resources are available to students?</summary>

#### Resources are available throughout programming activities and are set up to be used as needed, not read as a pre-reading or presented as a lecture. Students are not expected to already know all of the needed information when they start programming.  This structure reflects the ‚Äúdiscovery‚Äù model of the curriculum, but also supports students in the authentic use of resources and code documentation.

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
